      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Architecture and Quantization Benefits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LTX-2.3 22B Distilled INT8 employs post-training quantization to INT8 precision, reducing the model size by approximately 75% compared to FP32 versions. This distillation process preserves core capabilities while enabling faster inference on standard hardware. For API teams, this translates to lower operational costs and improved throughput, especially in high-concurrency environments where resource efficiency is paramount."
          }
        ]
      },
